&lt;div class=&quot;content-intro&quot;&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;img style=&quot;display: block; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto; max-width: 100%;&quot; src=&quot;https://cdn.appdocs.com/files/client-files/ApplicantPro%20Orgs/TrellisWare%20Technologies%2C%20Inc/new1.jpg&quot; alt=&quot;&quot; width=&quot;632&quot;&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;TrellisWare launched in 2000 with an innovative culture striving to push technological boundaries in the area of wireless communications. We are now a worldwide leader in highly advanced algorithms, waveforms, and communications systems that range from small form factor radio products to fully integrated solutions.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;At TrellisWare, we connect passion with purpose and together we make an impact- on our careers, our company, and the world. And you can too. If you love to innovate and collaborate in a dynamic environment where boundaries are being pushed, you belong at TrellisWare. Where the opportunity to serve is not a challenge but a gift.&amp;nbsp;Where you’re never going alone. &lt;strong&gt;Because there’s too much at stake to go solo.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;p&gt;Our Business Development Team is seeking an &lt;strong&gt;Account Manager, Asia-Pacific Region, &lt;/strong&gt;based in the Philippines.&lt;strong&gt; &lt;/strong&gt;You would be responsible for all of TrellisWare’s international business development activities in the region.&amp;nbsp;A strong understanding of Asia-Pacific markets and the sales process and an ability to qualify/prioritize opportunities will be keys to success for this role. Additional responsibilities include identifying and vetting new opportunities, developing and maintaining relationships with customers and partners in the Asia-Pacific region, validating customers&#39; funding, identifying contract vehicles, understanding buying trends within different customer segments, and providing useful market information back to TrellisWare to determine market expansions/contractions and new product introductions.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The &lt;strong&gt;essential duties and responsibilities&lt;/strong&gt; include:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Strategy:&lt;/strong&gt; &lt;em&gt;Develops and&lt;/em&gt; &lt;em&gt;executes the international business development strategy for the Asia-Pacific region in line with strategic and marketing goals.&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Identifies new opportunities and acquisition programs.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Analyzes and articulates new business/market opportunities in terms of market size, growth trends, and competition.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Leads initiatives to develop new markets in line with strategic goals.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Presents strategy and activity updates to senior leadership.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Sales &amp;amp; Business Development: &lt;/strong&gt;&lt;em&gt;Identifies and manages sales channels and customer relationships.&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Develops marketing messaging for conferences, trade shows, and advertising campaigns / publicity in line with strategic focus.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Provides sales leadership for named accounts and/or territories.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Meets business development objectives for contract awards for established TrellisWare and vendor partner products.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Maintains a 3x target pipeline on a rolling 12-month basis and actionable 6-month forecast.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Identifies and leads capture efforts, to include product demonstrations, customer meetings, proposal writing, and costing inputs based on internal TWT requirements and customer budgets.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Develops and maintains relationships with customers and vendor partners at various levels from initial contact through fulfillment.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Identifies and attends key conferences and trade shows.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
